title: Personal goals of health/fitness club members 2014
summary: This is a bar chart. It shows Percentage of respondents for 13 number of Reasons to Reasons for joinings.
The Percentage of respondents is highest at Reasons to Reasons for joining To stay healthy and lowest at Reasons to Reasons for joining To gain weight.
Reasons to Reasons for joining To stay healthy has 21.33 times more Percentage of respondents than Reasons to Reasons for joining To gain weight which is has the lowest.
min_summary: This bar chart has 13 columns on the x axis representing Reasons to Reasons for joining, and Percentage of respondents in each Reasons to Reasons for joining on the y axis.
Reasons to Reasons for joining To stay healthy has the highest Percentage of respondents and To gain weight has the lowest Percentage of respondents.

max_summary: This is a bar chart. It shows Percentage of respondents for 13 number of Reasons to Reasons for joinings.
The Percentage of respondents is highest at Reasons to Reasons for joining To stay healthy and lowest at Reasons to Reasons for joining To gain weight.
Second maximum Percentage of respondents is found at Reasons to Reasons for joining To feel better about myself.
Reasons to Reasons for joining To gain weight has 21.33 times less Percentage of respondents than Reasons to Reasons for joining To stay healthy which is the highest.

Reasons to Reasons for joining To stay healthy is higher than any other Reasons to Reasons for joinings with value 64.0, followed by To feel better about myself, and To stay in shape. Down to Reasons to Reasons for joining To gain weight with the lowest value 3.0.
Reasons to Reasons for joining To look better, and To lose weight share the same value 45.0.
The Reasons to Reasons for joining To gain weight has 1.78 times less Percentage of respondents than average.
The Percentage of respondents is 468.0 if we add up values of all Reasons to Reasons for joinings.
